Wash and dry all produce. Adjust racks to middle and upper position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Strip and finely chop enough @Rosemary{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems to give you 2 TBSP. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{5%teaspoon}, half the chopped rosemary, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven on middle rack until tender and crisped, about ~{30%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

In a #shallow dish{}, stir together @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup}, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, @Panko Breadcrumbs{1%cup}, remaining chopped rosemary, and a large drizzle of oil. Season with salt and pepper. Brush 2 TBSP @Sour Cream{8%tablespoon} all over @Pork Tenderloin{24%ounce} and season with salt and pepper. Coat pork all over with panko mixture, pressing to adhere. Place on another lightly oiled #baking sheet{}.

Roast pork in oven on upper rack until crust is golden brown and meat is cooked to desired doneness, ~{25-30%minutes}—roasting time may vary; it may need to cook longer. Let pork rest for ~{5%minutes} after removing from oven, then cut into thin slices.

> If crust doesn't brown, heat broiler to high and broil until browned on surface, about 2 minutes.

Zest 1 tsp zest from @Lemon{1}, then cut into halves. Halve and core @Apple{1}, then slice into thin half-moons. In a #small bowl{}, combine lemon zest, remaining sour cream, and up to 1 tsp lemon juice (use less to taste). Season with salt and pepper.

In a #large bowl{}, toss together @Mixed Greens{4%ounce}, apple, @Dried Cranberries{2%ounce}, @Walnuts{1%ounce}, @Olive Oil{2%tablespoon}, and a squeeze of lemon, to taste. Season with salt and pepper. Divide pork, potatoes, and salad between plates. Serve with sauce on the side for dipping potatoes and pork.